comments.text:
BEND YOUR KNEE

How do You feel Lord, when You we shun

As so many of us at some point have done?

Our faith is ridiculed by athiests poking fun

Your Son endured the cross so we may come

Come to You whose arms are outstretched 

Who forgives the unforgivable and says

I have longed for this moment and yes

Yes you are Mine and I confess

I shall pursue you all the days of your life

BUT it is you who has the freedom to choose

To accept what I am offering or lose

Eternal life beside my throne

Or to burn in hell alone

For once in hell you cannot return

You'll gnash your teeth and beg

Too late - you had your whole life to repent

So soften your heart and bend your knee

For as God says

I AM, I CAN, I WILL, I DO

Fulfill my promises to you!"


By Terry Blanckenberg - South Africa
